Sentencas: A combination of electroless and electrolytic techniques is used to incorporate nickel into a porous Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.90 scaffold.
Titulo: Metallizing porous scaffolds as an alternative fabrication method for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: First a porous backbone was screen printed into a YSZ electrolyte using an ink that contains sacrificial pore formers.
Titulo: Metallizing porous scaffolds as an alternative fabrication method for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: Once sintered, the scaffold was coated with silver using Tollens' reaction followed by electrodeposition of nickel in a Watts bath.
Titulo: Metallizing porous scaffolds as an alternative fabrication method for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: At high temperatures the silver forms droplets enabling direct contact between the gadolinia-doped ceria and nickel.
Titulo: Metallizing porous scaffolds as an alternative fabrication method for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: Using impedance spectroscopy analysis in a symmetrical cell a total area specific resistance of 1 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C in 97% H-2 with 3% H2O was found, indicating the potential of this fabrication method for scaling up.
Titulo: Metallizing porous scaffolds as an alternative fabrication method for solid oxide fuel cell anodes
